Introduction

Terazono Keita, popularly known as Keita, is a Japanese rapper and composer signed with Rain Company. He plays the roles of the main rapper, dancer, and singer in the boy group Ciipher and also leads the project boy group EVNNE.

He first appeared in the survival show YG TREASURE BOX by YG Entertainment. In 2021, he debuted as a member of Ciipher. In 2023, he participated in Boys Planet. Although he did not make it in the final lineup, Keita became a member of the spinoff group EVNNE managed by Jellyfish Entertainment.
